.TH CCUTTER "1" "" "CheeseCutter-Extended 0.3.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ccutter \- SID music editor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ccutter
[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR]... [\fI\,FILE\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
CheeseCutter\-Extended 0.3.0, based on CheeseCutter 2.9.
.PP
CheeseCutter (C) 2009\-17 Abaddon. Released under GNU GPL.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-b\fR [value]
Set playback buffer size (def=2048)
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-full\fR
Start in fullscreen mode
.TP
\fB\-nofp\fR
Do not use resid\-fp emulation
.TP
\fB\-fpr\fR [x]
Specify filter preset. x = 0..16 for 6581 and 0..1 for 8580
.TP
\fB\-i\fR
Disable resid interpolation (use fast mode instead)
.TP
\fB\-l\fR
Enable VIC\-II badline timing emulation
.TP
\fB\-m\fR [0|1]
Specify SID model for reSID (6581/8580) (def=0)
.TP
\fB\-n\fR
Enable NTSC mode
.TP
\fB\-r\fR [value]
Set playback frequency (def=48000)
.TP
\fB\-y\fR
Use YUV video overlay
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show this help and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-height\fR [rows]
Set sequencer height in rows (min=40, max=64); disables autoscale
.TP
\fB\-\-width\fR [cols]
Set UI width in columns (min=160, max=200); disables autoscale
.TP
\fB\-\-dump\-keys\fR
Print the keyboard reference as Markdown and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-dump\-man\fR
Print the man page (roff) to stdout and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-ultimate\fR [IP]
Play on a C64 Ultimate (1541U/Ultimate64) at IP over its REST API
.TP
\fB\-\-ultimate\-port\fR [n]
REST API port for \-\-ultimate (def=80)
.TP
\fB\-\-vice\fR
Play on a VICE x64sc (launches x64sc from PATH). \-\-vice=host:port attaches to a running \-binarymonitor; \-\-vice=/path/x64sc launches that binary
.TP
\fB\-\-vice\-port\fR [n]
Binary\-monitor port for \-\-vice (def=6502)
.TP
\fB\-\-verbose\fR
Enable verbose logging
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBCHEESECUTTER_ULTIMATE_PASSWORD\fR
If set, sent as the X\-Password header on every C64 Ultimate REST request (firmware 3.12+).
.SH KEYS
In the editor press F12 for context help, or run ccutter \-\-dump\-keys for the full reference. Shift\-F10 saves the current subtune as a self\-running .prg.
.SH SEE ALSO
ct2util(1)
